'''Rob Johnson''' (also known under various pseudonyms, including '''Freshbread''') is a [[Canada|Canadian]] musician currently based in [[Vancouver, British Columbia]].  He played bass guitar in the [[punk rock|punk]] and [[alternative rock]] bands [[SNFU]] and the [[Wheat Chiefs]], in addition to recording his own [[hip hop]] and [[hard rock]] music in various incarnations.

==Career==
Johnson joined the influential<ref>http://www.push.ca/blogs/andrewsk/archive/2009/08/19/the-undeniable-influence-of-skate-punk-and-snfu.aspx</ref><ref>http://www.troopertribute.com/snfu.htm</ref> SNFU in 1992 at the age of 20,<ref name=cbc>http://radio3.cbc.ca/#/bands/FRESHBREAD</ref>  while also associated with the Wheat Chiefs, a side project featuring several of the group's members.  He played with the former group for ten years, appearing on four albums and touring extensively.  After leaving SNFU in 2002, he began the hard rock band Air Raid Siren with drummer [[Sean Stubbs]].<ref name=cbc />

In 1999, Johnson began his hip-hop career under the Freshbread moniker.<ref name=cbc />  He released the ''Big Boss Battle'' album in 2002.<ref>http://www.hour.ca/music/spin.aspx?iIDDisque=1755</ref>

